My aim is to write posts on topics such as programming tutorials, thoughts about a particular technology, and whatever else comes to mind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I started this blog using &lt;a href="http://docs.getpelican.com/en/stable/"&gt;Pelican&lt;/a&gt;, a static site generator written in Python.  The site is hosted on Github Pages.  Github Pages hosts static websites for free and it is
&lt;a href="https://www.savjee.be/2017/10/Static-website-hosting-who-is-fastest/"&gt;fast&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pelican supports Markdown, which is really nice.  In general, it makes it straightforward for a developer to build a blog easily, assuming you are comfortable with the command line and Python.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here's a random Python code snippet that draws a snowflake using Python's turtle library (it has nothing to do with this post. Just wanted to demonstrate how a code block looks using markdown):&lt;/p&gt;
